<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06189149 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06189149 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Map; MAP: Mercury News; Genoa  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  HISTORY; FOUND; NORTH-AMERICA; FESTIVAL; WORLD; LIST  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  THE quincentenary of Christopher Columbus' first voyage to the New World willbe celebrated all over the world. Among the planned events:;    (check) EXPO'92 -- Seville, Spain, April 20 to Oct. 12, 1992. The theme is &quot;The Age ofDiscovery,&quot; and the spirit of Columbus will be very much in evidence. The fairwill take place on an island in the Guadalquivir River, opposite the old partof the city. The island is being fitted with pavilions, parks, theaters,sports arenas and a hotel complex, and a monastery in which Columbus lived foreight years is being renovated.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Travel  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  COLUMBUS CALENDAR  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Cover StorySee also related stories on P. 1T, 7T, 8T, 9T and 10T of this sectionThe Great Columbus Chase  </MEMO><TEXT>     (check) COLOMBO '92 -- Genoa, May 15-Aug. 15. Another Expo, this oneconcentrating on maritime activities and on Columbus himself.;    (check)GRAND REGATTA COLUMBUS '92 -- Puerto Rico, May-June 1992. A fleet of tallsailing ships and hundreds of pleasure craft will sail from Cadiz and arriveat San Juan in May 1992. There will be events in San Juan June 10-14.;   (check) 1992 SUMMER OLYMPICS -- Barcelona, July 25-Aug. 9, 1992. The games arededicated to Columbus.;    (check) CIRCA 1492: Art in the Age of Exploration-- National Gallery, Washington, D.C., Oct. 12, 1991 through Jan. 12, 1992. Itwill include more than 400 paintings, sculptures, drawings, maps, screens,scrolls, scientific instruments and other objects from the period of hislifetime, borrowed from about 20 countries.;    (check) AmeriFlora '92 --Beginning April 3, 1992, Columbus, Ohio. The 17-day, indoor GrandInternational Floral Exposition is an international garden festival being heldas part of the 500th anniversary celebrations. The city thought about aworld's fair, but decided to go with a huge flower show instead.;    (check)&quot;YEAR OF DISCOVERY&quot; -- Beginning Oct. 12, 1991, throughout South Carolina.Among the programs scheduled are the &quot;Discovery Photo Album&quot; modeled after thephoto book &quot;A Day in the Life of the United States.&quot; Citizens will be asked totake pictures of unusual or historic things in their county Oct. 12, 1991. Thephotos will be used to create a state photo album.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910707  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  10T  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  MAP  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  360  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday July 7, 199100189149,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>